1 1. The second first Tuesday of February March in any year;
2 2. The first Tuesday of April in any year third Tuesday in
3 June;
4 3. The date of any regularly scheduled statewide state or
5 federal election in an even-numbered year fourth Tuesday in August;
6 and
7 4. The second first Tuesday of September in an odd-numbered
8 year;
9 5. The second Tuesday of November in an odd-numbered year; and
10 6. The second Tuesday of June of an odd-numbered year for a
11 special election to fill a vacancy after the first Monday in
12 November.
13 C. Except as otherwise provided by law or by Section 1 of this
14 act, no and with the declaration of an emergency by the Governor
15 permitting a special election, an election for any purpose other
16 than to fill a vacancy in an elective office shall may be held by
17 any county, school district, technology center school district,
18 municipality, fire protection district or other political
19 subdivision authorized to call elections except on:
20 1. The second Tuesday of January, February, May, June, July,
21 August, September, October and November and the first Tuesday in
22 March and April in odd-numbered years; provided, a municipality with
23 a population in excess of two hundred fifty thousand (250,000)
24 persons, according to the most recent Federal Decennial Census, may
