1 also hold an election on the second Tuesday of December in odd-
2 numbered years; and
3 2. The second Tuesday of January and February, the first
4 Tuesday in March and April, the third Tuesday in June, the fourth
5 Tuesday in August, and the first Tuesday after the first Monday in
6 November of any even-numbered year.
7 D. In the event that a regular or special election date occurs
8 on an official state holiday, the election shall be scheduled for
9 the next following Tuesday. In the event that any day of a
10 candidate filing period occurs on a Saturday, Sunday or any official
11 state holiday, that day of the filing period shall be scheduled for
12 the next business day.
13 E. Notwithstanding any other provision of law or any provision
14 of a municipal charter, any municipality, school district,
15 technology center district, county, rural fire protection district,
16 or any other entity seeking to hold a regular or special election to
17 be conducted by a county election board on the same date as a
18 regular or special federal or state election, shall file the
19 resolution calling for the election with the county election board
20 secretary no later than seventy-five (75) days prior to the election
21 date. A candidate filing period of three (3) days, if so required
22 by the resolution, shall begin no later than ten (10) days following
23 the deadline to file the resolution with the secretary of the county
24 election board; provided, the filing period for such municipal
